race.comment: SPANISH FOX (3) returned to form last time out when third over this trip at Eagle Farm. Doubt he will find this any tougher so with a cosy run assured out of the inside alley he should be right in the finish. RED DEFCON (5) will find this easier than the Class 6 she contested at Eagle Farm last Saturday. Made up plenty of ground to grab fourth at the end of 1400m that day - the extra furlong looks perfect fourth-up. Just three wins from 35 is the knock. TUHINGA (6) led but found a couple better over this course and distance recently. Honest veteran with each-way claims. I'M HEROIC (8) wasn't beaten far last time out and should be peaking after three runs back from a break.
